parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to property damage and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often when the driver is attempting to stop or slow down. The accelerator pedal may not return to its normal position
and the brakes may be ineffective in stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle to stop can cause accidents, injuries, and property damage. It can also lead to a loss of control and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to stop or slows down unexpectedly
even when the brakes are applied. The vehicle may lurch forward or accelerate suddenly
making it difficult for the driver to maintain control.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle control system can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents. It can also lead to property damage and potentially life-threatening situations.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often when the driver is attempting to stop or slow down. The accelerator pedal may not return to its normal position
and the brakes may be ineffective in stopping the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Alternator Failure Leading to Sudden Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to a loss of steering and braking ability, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or shuts down
the battery drains rapidly
the vehicle loses power
the engine stops running
the vehicle is unable to steer or brake.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Failure Causing Unintended Vehicle Movement
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rolls or moves without warning
the vehicle fails to start
the battery is dead
the vehicle's electrical systems malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delayed acceleration and surging can cause the vehicle to hesitate or lurch forward, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or delays acceleration
the vehicle surges or lurches forward
the vehicle fails to accelerate smoothly
the powertrain malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
occupants are not restrained
and injuries or fatalities occur.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, as the vehicle may accelerate unexpectedly and uncontrollably.
symptoms: The engine revs and the vehicle accelerates forward without driver input
often when the brake pedal is pressed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty occupancy sensor can lead to incorrect airbag deployment or failure to deploy, which can result in injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The occupancy sensor lights up or indicates that the seat is occupied when it is not
